Fig. 20
). Dentes with 18–39 spines; basal setae (following
Szeptycki 1973
) bs 1 and bs 2 spiny and multilaterally ciliate, bs 1 slightly shorter than bs 2 ; proximal-inner seta (pi) ciliate, apparently thinner, slender and longer than bs 1 and bs 2 (
Fig. 21
